4 <Section 1. SHORT TITLE. This Act shall be known and may be
5 cited as the “Center for Intellectual Freedom Act”.
6 Sec. 2. NEW SECTION. 263C.1 Definitions.
7 As used in this chapter, unless the context otherwise
8 requires:
9 1. “Board” means the state board of regents.
10 2. “Center” means the center for intellectual freedom
11 established by section 263C.2.
12 3. “Regents institution” means an institution specified in
13 section 262.7, subsections 1 through 3.
14 4. “University” means the state university of Iowa.
15 Sec. 3. NEW SECTION. 263C.2 Center for intellectual
16 freedom.
17 1. A center for intellectual freedom is established as an
18 independent academic center under the board at the university.
19 2. The center shall conduct teaching and research in the
20 historical ideas, traditions, and texts that have shaped the
21 American constitutional order and society.
22 3. The board may name the center in accordance with any
23 philanthropic naming policies or practices of the board or
24 university.
25 Sec. 4. NEW SECTION. 263C.3 Functions of the center.
26 1. The center shall provide scholarship in all of the
27 following subjects:
28 a. The texts and major debates that form the intellectual
29 foundation of free societies, especially that of the United
30 States.
31 b. The principles, ideals, and institutions of the American
32 constitutional order.
33 c. The foundations of responsible leadership and informed
34 citizenship.
35 2. The center shall offer university-wide programming
