1 related to the values of free speech and civil discourse.
2 3. The center shall work to do all of the following:
3 a. Expand the intellectual diversity of the university’s
4 academic community.
5 b. Foster civic engagement among university students and
6 faculty.
7 c. Coordinate with the center for cyclone civics at Iowa
8 state university and the center for civic education at the
9 university of northern Iowa to enable academic offerings that
10 may be offered to students at any of the regents institutions
11 either in person or online.
12 4. The center, in collaboration with any of the regents
13 institutions, may offer courses; develop certificate, minor,
14 and major programs as well as graduate programs; and offer
15 degrees.
16 5. The center shall offer at least one three-semester
17 credit hour course in American history and civil government.
18 If a regents institution has established general education
19 requirements for undergraduate students that include an
20 American heritage course requirement, the center shall ensure
21 that the course satisfies that requirement. The center shall
22 coordinate with the center for cyclone civics at Iowa state
23 university and the center for civic education at the university
24 of northern Iowa to ensure that the course is offered to
25 students at each regents institution either in person or
26 online.
27 Sec. 5. NEW SECTION. 263C.4 Bylaws.
28 The center shall establish bylaws governing the center
29 subject to the approval of the board. In addition to any
30 other bylaws established, the bylaws must include all of the
31 following requirements, which shall take precedence over any
32 other requirements in the bylaws:
33 1. The center shall educate students by means of free, open,
34 and rigorous intellectual inquiry to seek the truth.
35 2. The center affirms its duty to equip students with
