1 the skills, habits, and dispositions of mind they need to
2 reach their own informed conclusions on matters of social and
3 political importance.
4 3. The center affirms the value of intellectual diversity
5 in higher education and aspires to enhance the intellectual
6 diversity of the university.
7 4. The center affirms a commitment to create a community
8 dedicated to an ethic of civil and free inquiry, which respects
9 the intellectual freedom of each member, supports individual
10 capacities for growth, and welcomes the differences of opinion
11 that naturally exist in a public university community.
12 Sec. 6. NEW SECTION. 263C.5 Funding —— use.
13 1. The center may accept and administer private and
14 external donations and gifts. The university of Iowa center
15 for advancement shall be the designated foundation for
16 philanthropic gifts or funding for the center.
17 2. Any moneys appropriated to the center, and any private
18 and external donations to the center, shall be used only for
19 the direct operation of the center.
20 3. Any additional funding required to operate the center
21 shall be proportionally provided by the regents institutions,
22 subject to approval of the board.
23 Sec. 7. NEW SECTION. 263C.6 Center faculty.
24 The university shall employ tenure-eligible faculty members
25 to provide instruction through the center. The university
26 shall incrementally increase the number of such faculty to five
27 based on market research and student demand. Faculty members
28 appointed to the center may hold joint appointments to other
29 academic units of the university. Faculty members who are not
30 affiliated with the center shall have no authority to approve,
31 deny, or modify the terms of appointment of faculty to the
32 center.
33 Sec. 8. NEW SECTION. 263C.7 Advisory council.
34 1. No later than December 31, 2025, the board shall appoint
35 an advisory council for the center.
