1 2. The board shall appoint a minimum of nine members to the
2 council. A majority of the members appointed to the council
3 shall constitute a quorum. No more than one member of the
4 council may be an employee of the university.
5 3. The board shall determine the initial length of each
6 member’s term in accordance with this subsection. A majority
7 of the members initially appointed to the council shall serve
8 initial terms of four years. The remaining initially appointed
9 members shall serve initial terms of two years. The board
10 shall appoint new members to fill vacancies on the council in
11 accordance with this section.
12 Sec. 9. NEW SECTION. 263C.8 Appointment of director.
13 1. The advisory council established under section 263C.7
14 shall conduct a nationwide search for candidates for the
15 director of the center. The council shall adhere to all
16 relevant state and federal laws in conducting the search. The
17 council shall submit finalists for the position to the board.
18 The board, upon approval of a candidate, shall appoint the
19 candidate as the director. All subsequent directors shall be
20 chosen in the same manner.
21 2. The director shall have the academic standing to be
22 eligible for tenure at a regents institution.
23 Sec. 10. NEW SECTION. 263C.9 Duties of director.
24 1. The director of the center shall have the sole and
25 exclusive authority to manage the recruitment and hiring
26 process, and to extend offers for employment, of the center
27 and to terminate employment of all staff of the center in
28 accordance with state and federal law.
29 2. The director shall conduct a market assessment to
30 determine course demand and the number of faculty required to
31 meet any unmet needs of the center and may conduct additional
32 market assessments as needed. A market assessment shall
33 include the subjects described in section 263C.3, subsections 1
34 and 2.
35 3. The director shall have the authority to invite guest
